-- PetroEcuador Said to Extend Refinery Shutdown, Repairs Until Oct. 8
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2010-09-28T16:29:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/petroecuador-said-to-extend-repairs-at-esmeraldas-gas-refinery-by-a-week.html
PetroEcuador, the state-owned oil
company, will complete repairs at its  Esmeraldas refinery  by
Oct. 8, about a week longer than previously forecast, a refinery
official said.  Repairs to the refineryâ€™s catalytic cracker unit, which
produces about 10,000 barrels of high-octane gasoline per day,
were previously scheduled to be finished by Sept. 30, the
official who declined to be identified because of company policy
said today in a telephone interview. The repairs are taking
longer than expected because damage in the unit was worse than
originally thought, the official said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
